
[1]testoon

   TESTOON', n. A silver coin in Italy and Portugal. In Florence, the
   testoon is worth two lire or three paoli, about seventeen pence
   sterling, or thirty two cents. At Lisbon, the testoon, as a money of
   account, is valued at 100 rees, about seven pence sterling, or twelve
   and a half cents.
